Introduction

Aria.J, also known as Jeong Boyoung, is a South Korean ballad singer, broadcaster, and internet personality.

She is active as a VJ on global live streaming apps BIGO Live, HelloTalk, and TikTok, and belongs to the Olive Entertainment family. She won the BIGO Live Korea Official Logo Song Tournament in 2020, debuted with the album In, and broadcasts Korean Wave content to HelloTalk and TikTok users.

With her passion for singing, she left Ulsan when she was 14 years old and moved to Seoul. She faced many challenges, such as long commutes, failed auditions, and diplomatic issues, and almost gave up on their dream. However, she managed to find a job as an artist at the Korea-China Private Cooperation Forum and performed in both countries.

In 2018, she debuted as a musical actor and BIGO Live VJ. She performed at events like the Korea-China Forum and the National Defense Gugak Association. She won the BIGO Live Logo Song Tournament in 2020. She released three singles: BAD, Love Is Everything, and Such a Love. She also collaborated with Piano VJ Mask Black on a project album. She has powerful vocals and charisma on stage.

With a new vocal style, she released “Such a Love” in 2022. She gained popularity on HelloTalk and released her first dance song, “Reset”. She participated in events and contests such as the Summit Play, the Super Influencer Awards, and the Time Capsule Concert. In 2023, she also made an appearance on KBC Chicago News.
